messages.content: What is the purpose of the ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio custom node?
The ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio custom node is designed to create empty latents for Stable Cascade in ComfyUI.
What is the default incrementation value for width and height in the ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio custom node?
The default incrementation value for width and height in the ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio custom node is 64.
Can you lock the aspect ratio in the ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio custom node?
Yes, the ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio custom node provides the possibility to lock the aspect ratio. Changing the width or the height will update the other dimension accordingly.
What happens when you switch width and height at execution in the ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio custom node?
When you switch width and height at execution in the ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio custom node, the change is not displayed in the node, but is taken into account at run time.
How does the ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio custom node handle batch sizes for stage_c and stage_b?
In the ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio custom node, stage_c and stage_b batch sizes are separated into two widgets to allow the use of the Latent From Batch node.
How can you install the ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio custom node?

To install the ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio custom node, you need to git clone the repo in the `ComfyUI/custom_nodes` folder using the command: `git clone https://github.com/Guillaume-Fgt/ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio.git`.
Where can you find the ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio custom node after installation?
After installation, you can find the ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio custom node under `latent/Stable Cascade Latent Ratio`.
